{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exempt people with phobias of needles from any Covid-19 vaccination requirements",
        "additional_details": "For 27 years I have carried the effects of a traumatic vaccine event. After 10 yrs of therapy, I am still struggling and am on my 3rd attempt at dose 1. People with needle phobias have spent 18 months terrified of Covid and the vaccine.\r\n \r\nI don't qualify for medical exemption, but the lack of exemption is unjust and counterproductive: it dehumanises and adds pressure to attempts.",
        "background": "The Government should create legal exemptions for people with needle phobias from all requirements relating to vaccination against Covid-19, so that are treated no differently to people who have been fully vaccinated.",
